Description: 
Inside Sport tackles the taboo issue of mental illness, 
and explores the dark side of sporting fame and fortune. 
Marcus Trescothick, Kelly Holmes, Frank Bruno, Paul 
Gascoigne and Neil Lennon are just some of the big 
names who have been hit by depression in recent years.
Gabby Logan examines the stigma that still surrounds 
mental health issues, and asks whether we ask too much 
of our sporting heroes. Featuring Ashes winner 
Trescothick, former heavyweight champion Bruno, Celtic 
icon Lennon and All Black legend John Kirwan.
